      • COORDINATES

        private static final Coordinate[][] COORDINATES
        Static matrix of all coordinats.

        The number of coordinates is small, and all coordinates can be held in memoery at all times. This would prevent duplicate instances of the same coordinate, and would save some garbage collection.

      • get

        public static Coordinate get(java.lang.String name)
        Returns a coordinate by its name, or null if the name is invalid.

        A coordinate name is the algebric notation name of the square, where the file is in lower-case. For example: "e4".

      • add

        public Coordinate add(int files,
             int ranks)
        Tries to add the given files and ranks to the coodinate.
        Parameters:
        files - The number of files to add (may be negative).
        ranks - The number of ranks to add (may be negative).
        Returns:
        The coordinate with the added files and ranks, or null if the new coordinate is outside the board.
